===subject:Topic 11
===from:Nahelia Schoonmaker
===date:Mon Apr 21 22:09:48 2003
===message:I think that outside intervention is a good thing only when it is necessary. I think that it was necessary in the situation with Timor. The people of East Timor were given the choice to become free. They were not told if you choose to be free you will be gunned down. If they were not going to be freed then why were they even given the choice? If someone had not come in and intervened there might not be any people left in Timor. I think that intervention should stay local unless it is such a big issue that it can not be solved locally. In any event that occurs (including the war with Iraq) the public does not see every issue that has to be dealt with, and I don't think that the UN is doing their job badly, but I also don't think it matters who supervises the intervention, as long as it is done.    
